17765: /**
17766:  * Package syntax parses regular expressions into parse trees and compiles
17767:  * parse trees into programs. Most clients of regular expressions will use the
17768:  * facilities of package [regexp] (such as [regexp.Compile] and [regexp.Match]) instead of this package.
17769:  * 
17770:  * # Syntax
17771:  * 
17772:  * The regular expression syntax understood by this package when parsing with the [Perl] flag is as follows.
17773:  * Parts of the syntax can be disabled by passing alternate flags to [Parse].
17774:  * 
17775:  * Single characters:
17776:  * 
17777:  * ```
17778:  * 	.              any character, possibly including newline (flag s=true)
17779:  * 	[xyz]          character class
17780:  * 	[^xyz]         negated character class
17781:  * 	\d             Perl character class
17782:  * 	\D             negated Perl character class
17783:  * 	[[:alpha:]]    ASCII character class
17784:  * 	[[:^alpha:]]   negated ASCII character class
17785:  * 	\pN            Unicode character class (one-letter name)
17786:  * 	\p{Greek}      Unicode character class
17787:  * 	\PN            negated Unicode character class (one-letter name)
17788:  * 	\P{Greek}      negated Unicode character class
17789:  * ```
17790:  * 
17791:  * Composites:
17792:  * 
17793:  * ```
17794:  * 	xy             x followed by y
17795:  * 	x|y            x or y (prefer x)
17796:  * ```
17797:  * 
17798:  * Repetitions:
17799:  * 
17800:  * ```
17801:  * 	x*             zero or more x, prefer more
17802:  * 	x+             one or more x, prefer more
17803:  * 	x?             zero or one x, prefer one
17804:  * 	x{n,m}         n or n+1 or ... or m x, prefer more
17805:  * 	x{n,}          n or more x, prefer more
17806:  * 	x{n}           exactly n x
17807:  * 	x*?            zero or more x, prefer fewer
17808:  * 	x+?            one or more x, prefer fewer
17809:  * 	x??            zero or one x, prefer zero
17810:  * 	x{n,m}?        n or n+1 or ... or m x, prefer fewer
17811:  * 	x{n,}?         n or more x, prefer fewer
17812:  * 	x{n}?          exactly n x
17813:  * ```
17814:  * 
17815:  * Implementation restriction: The counting forms x{n,m}, x{n,}, and x{n}
17816:  * reject forms that create a minimum or maximum repetition count above 1000.
17817:  * Unlimited repetitions are not subject to this restriction.
17818:  * 
17819:  * Grouping:
17820:  * 
17821:  * ```
17822:  * 	(re)           numbered capturing group (submatch)
17823:  * 	(?P<name>re)   named & numbered capturing group (submatch)
17824:  * 	(?<name>re)    named & numbered capturing group (submatch)
17825:  * 	(?:re)         non-capturing group
17826:  * 	(?flags)       set flags within current group; non-capturing
17827:  * 	(?flags:re)    set flags during re; non-capturing
17828:  * 
17829:  * 	Flag syntax is xyz (set) or -xyz (clear) or xy-z (set xy, clear z). The flags are:
17830:  * 
17831:  * 	i              case-insensitive (default false)
17832:  * 	m              multi-line mode: ^ and $ match begin/end line in addition to begin/end text (default false)
17833:  * 	s              let . match \n (default false)
17834:  * 	U              ungreedy: swap meaning of x* and x*?, x+ and x+?, etc (default false)
17835:  * ```
17836:  * 
17837:  * Empty strings:
17838:  * 
17839:  * ```
17840:  * 	^              at beginning of text or line (flag m=true)
17841:  * 	$              at end of text (like \z not \Z) or line (flag m=true)
17842:  * 	\A             at beginning of text
17843:  * 	\b             at ASCII word boundary (\w on one side and \W, \A, or \z on the other)
17844:  * 	\B             not at ASCII word boundary
17845:  * 	\z             at end of text
17846:  * ```
17847:  * 
17848:  * Escape sequences:
17849:  * 
17850:  * ```
17851:  * 	\a             bell (== \007)
17852:  * 	\f             form feed (== \014)
17853:  * 	\t             horizontal tab (== \011)
17854:  * 	\n             newline (== \012)
17855:  * 	\r             carriage return (== \015)
17856:  * 	\v             vertical tab character (== \013)
17857:  * 	\*             literal *, for any punctuation character *
17858:  * 	\123           octal character code (up to three digits)
17859:  * 	\x7F           hex character code (exactly two digits)
17860:  * 	\x{10FFFF}     hex character code
17861:  * 	\Q...\E        literal text ... even if ... has punctuation
17862:  * ```
17863:  * 
17864:  * Character class elements:
17865:  * 
17866:  * ```
17867:  * 	x              single character
17868:  * 	A-Z            character range (inclusive)
17869:  * 	\d             Perl character class
17870:  * 	[:foo:]        ASCII character class foo
17871:  * 	\p{Foo}        Unicode character class Foo
17872:  * 	\pF            Unicode character class F (one-letter name)
17873:  * ```
17874:  * 
17875:  * Named character classes as character class elements:
17876:  * 
17877:  * ```
17878:  * 	[\d]           digits (== \d)
17879:  * 	[^\d]          not digits (== \D)
17880:  * 	[\D]           not digits (== \D)
17881:  * 	[^\D]          not not digits (== \d)
17882:  * 	[[:name:]]     named ASCII class inside character class (== [:name:])
17883:  * 	[^[:name:]]    named ASCII class inside negated character class (== [:^name:])
17884:  * 	[\p{Name}]     named Unicode property inside character class (== \p{Name})
17885:  * 	[^\p{Name}]    named Unicode property inside negated character class (== \P{Name})
17886:  * ```
17887:  * 
17888:  * Perl character classes (all ASCII-only):
17889:  * 
17890:  * ```
17891:  * 	\d             digits (== [0-9])
17892:  * 	\D             not digits (== [^0-9])
17893:  * 	\s             whitespace (== [\t\n\f\r ])
17894:  * 	\S             not whitespace (== [^\t\n\f\r ])
17895:  * 	\w             word characters (== [0-9A-Za-z_])
17896:  * 	\W             not word characters (== [^0-9A-Za-z_])
17897:  * ```
17898:  * 
17899:  * ASCII character classes:
17900:  * 
17901:  * ```
17902:  * 	[[:alnum:]]    alphanumeric (== [0-9A-Za-z])
17903:  * 	[[:alpha:]]    alphabetic (== [A-Za-z])
17904:  * 	[[:ascii:]]    ASCII (== [\x00-\x7F])
17905:  * 	[[:blank:]]    blank (== [\t ])
17906:  * 	[[:cntrl:]]    control (== [\x00-\x1F\x7F])
17907:  * 	[[:digit:]]    digits (== [0-9])
17908:  * 	[[:graph:]]    graphical (== [!-~] == [A-Za-z0-9!"#$%&'()*+,\-./:;<=>?@[\\\]^_`{|}~])
17909:  * 	[[:lower:]]    lower case (== [a-z])
17910:  * 	[[:print:]]    printable (== [ -~] == [ [:graph:]])
17911:  * 	[[:punct:]]    punctuation (== [!-/:-@[-`{-~])
17912:  * 	[[:space:]]    whitespace (== [\t\n\v\f\r ])
17913:  * 	[[:upper:]]    upper case (== [A-Z])
17914:  * 	[[:word:]]     word characters (== [0-9A-Za-z_])
17915:  * 	[[:xdigit:]]   hex digit (== [0-9A-Fa-f])
17916:  * ```
17917:  * 
17918:  * Unicode character classes are those in [unicode.Categories] and [unicode.Scripts].
17919:  */
