20936:    * associated Context is canceled, and a child process that exits but leaves
20937:    * its I/O pipes unclosed.
20938:    * 
20939:    * The WaitDelay timer starts when either the associated Context is done or a
20940:    * call to Wait observes that the child process has exited, whichever occurs
20941:    * first. When the delay has elapsed, the command shuts down the child process
20942:    * and/or its I/O pipes.
20943:    * 
20944:    * If the child process has failed to exit — perhaps because it ignored or
20945:    * failed to receive a shutdown signal from a Cancel function, or because no
20946:    * Cancel function was set — then it will be terminated using os.Process.Kill.
